# Deployment & CI/CD Guidelines

## Containerization
- Use multi-stage Docker builds for optimization
- Implement proper .dockerignore files
- Use official Node.js base images
- Optimize for production builds
- Implement proper health checks

## Docker Configuration
- Use Docker Compose for local development
- Implement proper environment variable handling
- Use Docker networks for service communication
- Implement proper volume management
- Use Docker secrets for sensitive data

## Kubernetes Deployment
- Use proper deployment manifests
- Implement horizontal pod autoscaling
- Use ConfigMaps and Secrets properly
- Implement proper ingress configuration
- Use proper resource limits and requests

## CI/CD Pipelines
- Use GitHub Actions for automation
- Implement proper testing stages
- Use semantic versioning
- Implement proper approval workflows
- Test deployments in staging environments

## Environment Management
- Use proper environment configurations
- Implement proper secrets management
- Use feature flags for gradual rollouts
- Implement proper backup strategies
- Monitor environment health

## Monitoring & Observability
- Implement proper logging strategies
- Use distributed tracing
- Monitor application metrics
- Implement proper alerting
- Use proper error tracking

## Security
- Scan container images for vulnerabilities
- Implement proper access controls
- Use network security policies
- Implement proper secrets rotation
- Monitor security events

## Performance
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Use CDN for static assets
- Optimize bundle sizes
- Implement proper compression
- Monitor performance metrics

## Rollback Strategies
- Implement proper rollback procedures
- Use blue-green deployments
- Implement canary deployments
- Monitor deployment health
- Have emergency rollback procedures

## Infrastructure as Code
- Use Terraform or Bicep for infrastructure
- Implement proper version control
- Use proper naming conventions
- Implement proper tagging strategies
- Document infrastructure decisions
